Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.07,0:02:21.53,Lyrics-Jap,,0,0,0,,{\fad(0,1550)}Believe your love
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.03,0:02:26.00,Ep Titles,,0,0,0,,{\pos(640,464.62)\blur0.334}Call and Eve
Dialogue: 10,0:02:31.71,0:02:34.45,Default,,0,0,0,,The results for the "Golden Future Cup" \Nare announced in November, right?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:34.45,0:02:35.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:35.27,0:02:38.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The decision is made at the \Nend of this month, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.30,0:02:38.51,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\c&H585B5C&\frz-12\fax0.1\blur1.003\fnHand Of Sean\fs36.769\move(666.667,314.204,666.667,397.769)\fsp3.008}Serialization Name Meeting
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.30,0:02:38.51,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\c&H2C2D2D&\frz-13\fax0.25\blur0.869\fnBakuShinn\fs53.481\move(833.333,50.139,833.333,133.704)}September Schedule
Dialogue: 10,0:02:38.01,0:02:42.44,Default,,0,0,0,,This time they're looking at 5000 questionnaires, \Nso I suppose they have to count all the votes again.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:42.44,0:02:42.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:43.81,0:02:44.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Again?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:44.72,0:02:45.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:45.51,0:02:48.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do they have to count all the votes again?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:48.18,0:02:49.53,Default,,0,0,0,,They're not really doing it {\i1}again{\i0}.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:49.89,0:02:54.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The 5000 vote count is just more \Naccurate than the real deal tally is.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:54.03,0:02:58.39,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a chance the 'like' percentages \Nand the overall ranks could change.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:58.39,0:03:00.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I sent in the questionnaire too.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:00.66,0:03:01.78,Default,,0,0,0,,But don't you think it's strange?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:02.66,0:03:03.74,Default,,0,0,0,,They're having the "Golden Future Cup" contest,
Dialogue: 10,0:03:03.74,0:03:07.54,Default,,0,0,0,,so why do you have to be compared \Nto the other series that are running?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:07.54,0:03:10.50,Default,,0,0,0,,They should just be ranking \Nthe entries against each other.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:11.08,0:03:15.47,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why they have the extra option \Nto either 'like' or 'not like' the entry.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:15.88,0:03:18.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It's important to know where the entry ranks overall.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:18.23,0:03:19.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not a simple decision.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:19.97,0:03:23.68,Default,,0,0,0,,But then isn't it possible to have an entry with \Na high 'like' percentage, but a low overall rank?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:23.68,0:03:24.89,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why they have the—
Dialogue: 10,0:03:24.89,0:03:25.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Shuujin!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:25.64,0:03:26.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The name.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:27.77,0:03:30.51,Default,,0,0,0,,We did everything we could.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:30.51,0:03:33.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Right now, we shouldn't worry about the \Ncontest anymore and just focus on the names
Dialogue: 10,0:03:33.86,0:03:35.21,Default,,0,0,0,,for December's serialization meeting.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:35.21,0:03:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You're right.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:36.52,0:03:40.29,Default,,0,0,0,,In any case, this way it's easier for the \Nediting department to make a decision.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:40.61,0:03:42.41,Default,,0,0,0,,They'll have more accurate information.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.49,0:03:49.50,Dates,,0,0,0,,{\fad(500,1000)}September 20th (Mon)
Dialogue: 10,0:03:50.71,0:03:52.55,Default,,0,0,0,,What are we supposed to do about this?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:53.92,0:03:54.86,Default,,0,0,0,,"Kiyoshi Knight."
Dialogue: 10,0:03:54.86,0:03:56.17,Default,,0,0,0,,1312 votes.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:56.17,0:03:57.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Third place.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:57.46,0:03:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,'Like' percentage: 79%.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:59.44,0:04:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,"Shady Detective Trap."
Dialogue: 10,0:04:00.72,0:04:02.26,Default,,0,0,0,,1321 votes.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:02.26,0:04:02.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Third place.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:03.34,0:04:05.30,Default,,0,0,0,,'Like' percentage: 76%.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:05.97,0:04:07.14,Default,,0,0,0,,"Hideout Door."
Dialogue: 10,0:04:07.14,0:04:08.22,Default,,0,0,0,,1103 votes.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:08.22,0:04:09.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Third place.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:09.22,0:04:11.23,Default,,0,0,0,,'Like' percentage: 73%.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:12.02,0:04:12.98,Default,,0,0,0,,"Colorfusical."
Dialogue: 10,0:04:12.98,0:04:14.44,Default,,0,0,0,,482 votes.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:14.44,0:04:15.74,Default,,0,0,0,,14th place.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:16.11,0:04:18.16,Default,,0,0,0,,'Like' percentage: 53%.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:19.15,0:04:22.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Not including "Colorfusical," \Nthese are pretty closely matched.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:22.65,0:04:26.92,Default,,0,0,0,,If everyone who selected 'like' also put \Nthe series in their top three favorites
Dialogue: 10,0:04:26.92,0:04:30.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and everyone who selected 'don't like' \Ndidn't, this would be so much easier.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:30.54,0:04:34.04,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why that option is totally unnecessary.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:34.04,0:04:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,But without it, we can't compare the \Nseries to figure out which is better.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:37.92,0:04:40.39,Default,,0,0,0,,We can't do that now, either.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:40.92,0:04:43.31,Default,,0,0,0,,If we just compare "Kiyoshi" and "Trap,"
Dialogue: 10,0:04:43.72,0:04:47.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd say "Trap" wins, since the average \Nvoting age was 14.3 years old.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:47.84,0:04:51.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, "Kiyoshi's" average of \N17.5 years old is too high.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:51.68,0:04:54.06,Default,,0,0,0,,That's more seinen manga \Nthan it is shounen manga.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:54.06,0:04:56.75,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're going to consider things like \Nthat, then in terms of gender ratio,
Dialogue: 10,0:04:56.75,0:04:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,, "Kiyoshi" is clearly the better shounen manga.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:58.40,0:05:02.53,Default,,0,0,0,,When you consider that over 90% of the votes \Ncame from male voters, this rank is really amazing.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:02.53,0:05:04.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Now isn't the time to be looking at the gender ratio.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:04.65,0:05:09.62,Default,,0,0,0,,"Trap" didn't have a very big female fan base \Neither and it still got more overall votes.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:09.62,0:05:11.74,Default,,0,0,0,,But "Kiyoshi" has a higher 'like' percentage.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:11.74,0:05:14.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And "Hideout Door" isn't out \Nof the running either, right?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:14.51,0:05:17.46,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't get very many female votes, but \Nthis story managed to get a lot of them.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:17.46,0:05:21.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It's true we don't have anything \Nlike this one in Jack right now.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:22.30,0:05:23.89,Default,,0,0,0,,It's already six o'clock?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:24.22,0:05:25.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It's almost night already!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:26.22,0:05:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The meeting still isn't over?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:27.76,0:05:31.13,Default,,0,0,0,,He said he'd call as soon as the \Nresults were announced, didn't he?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:31.13,0:05:32.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Calm down already.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:32.31,0:05:34.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? It's not like I'm beating myself up about it.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:34.81,0:05:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Beating mochi?
Comment: 0,0:05:35.06,0:05:39.40,TLNote,,0,0,0,,Note: Takagi uses the word "ochitsuki," meaning "to calm down," and Kaya uses a similar sounding word, "mochitsuki," meaning "to pound rice into mochi."
Dialogue: 10,0:05:36.48,0:05:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, right.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:37.10,0:05:38.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Smack! Smack!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:38.78,0:05:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Oi!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:39.60,0:05:40.98,Default-Italic,,0,0,0,,They're slow—
Dialogue: 10,0:05:40.98,0:05:44.43,Default,,0,0,0,,What's taking so long?! That \NYujiro didn't forget, did he?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:44.43,0:05:46.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess that wouldn't be like him—
Dialogue: 10,0:05:46.41,0:05:50.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I—I'm sure it'll probably be \Neither you or Ashirogi who gets it.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:50.58,0:05:52.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You never know.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:52.51,0:05:56.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Ashirogi and me both got second in the \Nreal deal results and you came in third,
Dialogue: 10,0:05:56.97,0:05:59.97,Default,,0,0,0,,but it wouldn't be all that strange for the \N5000 questionnaire results to be different.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:00.84,0:06:03.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Jeez, how many times do they \Nhave to count the votes anyway?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:06.42,0:06:08.18,Default-Italic,,0,0,0,,A different result, huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:16.81,0:06:18.52,Default,,0,0,0,,But we've already made it this far.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:18.52,0:06:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,No offense to you, but I'm gonna win this!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:21.44,0:06:23.65,Default-Italic,,0,0,0,,No, I'm going to win.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:24.57,0:06:25.79,Default-Italic,,0,0,0,,We're gonna win.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:30.78,0:06:31.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It's time!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:31.32,0:06:32.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi, this is Fukuda!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:33.16,0:06:33.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:33.78,0:06:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:34.48,0:06:35.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:35.24,0:06:36.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The "Golden Future Cup" is— {\1a&HFF&\3a&HFF&}Ours!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:36.91,0:06:39.29,Default,,0,0,0,,The "Golden Future Cup" is— Ours!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:37.54,0:06:38.88,Default-Alt2,,0,0,0,,We did it!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:39.29,0:06:40.33,Default,,0,0,0,,But guys, listen—
Dialogue: 10,0:06:40.33,0:06:41.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:41.71,0:06:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not just you, Fukuda—
Dialogue: 10,0:06:42.17,0:06:44.34,Default-Alt2,,0,0,0,,Fukuda-sensei, good job!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:44.46,0:06:45.51,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:46.21,0:06:47.31,Default,,0,0,0,,There are two winners?!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:48.68,0:06:51.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, yours and "Kiyoshi Knight."
Dialogue: 10,0:06:51.05,0:06:53.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The first tie in the contest's history?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:53.60,0:06:57.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, although this is only \Nthe sixth time we've held it.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:57.58,0:06:58.31,Default,,0,0,0,,At any rate—
Dialogue: 10,0:06:58.98,0:07:00.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Congratulations.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:04.94,0:07:07.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, we missed it this time, but—
Dialogue: 10,0:07:07.53,0:07:08.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:08.57,0:07:11.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So that means we can go ahead with this, right?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:11.24,0:07:12.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you so much!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:12.97,0:07:14.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you so much!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:14.08,0:07:15.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you so much!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:17.75,0:07:19.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Fukuda, congratulations.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:19.53,0:07:22.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not too happy about having \Nto share it with Ashirogi, though.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:23.20,0:07:24.54,Default,,0,0,0,,That aside—
Dialogue: 10,0:07:24.54,0:07:27.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess Niizuma-sensei's \Nprediction really came true.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:27.51,0:07:28.55,Default,,0,0,0,,A tie for first place.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:28.55,0:07:33.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm more surprised about Niizuma being \Nright than about the actual first ever tie.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:34.93,0:07:38.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if it was a tie, you got first! That's great!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:38.33,0:07:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, yeah.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:40.73,0:07:43.06,Default,,0,0,0,,That's great— right?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:44.52,0:07:45.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:45.52,0:07:50.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Although, this means that we'll be up against \NFukuda again in the serialization meeting.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:50.11,0:07:52.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, and Nakai's will probably be submitted, too.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:52.74,0:07:56.37,Default,,0,0,0,,You guys should stop talking about that.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:56.37,0:07:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,,For now, let's be happy, 'kay?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:58.24,0:07:59.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, sorry.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:59.87,0:08:00.62,Default,,0,0,0,,We are, though.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:00.62,0:08:02.25,Default,,0,0,0,,We are happy.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:02.25,0:08:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess you could say we're "updating our goals."
Dialogue: 10,0:08:05.42,0:08:06.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:06.79,0:08:08.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm so glad!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:08.34,0:08:09.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm so glad!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:09.42,0:08:11.01,Default-Italic,,0,0,0,,I gotta message Azuki.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:09.42,0:08:11.01,Default-Alt,,0,0,0,,Stop crying already.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:21.48,0:08:22.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:30.07,0:08:32.57,Default-Alt,,0,0,0,,I know you're happy, but you don't have to cry.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:32.57,0:08:34.91,Default-Alt,,0,0,0,,Yeah, but still—
Dialogue: 10,0:08:33.95,0:08:34.91,Default-Italic,,0,0,0,,It's here!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:35.57,0:08:36.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.20,0:08:40.16,Cellphone,,0,0,0,,{\move(820,80.222,820,-66.852)\fs76.88\fax-0.05\frz-7.7\blur1.337\c&H443B36&}Azuki Miho
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.20,0:08:40.16,Cellphone,,0,0,0,,{\move(640,280.778,640,133.704)\fs46.796\fax-0.02\frz-8.5\blur1.337\c&H423630&}Golden Future Cup results!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.20,0:08:40.16,Cellphone,,0,0,0,,{\move(473.333,486.013,473.333,338.939)\fs33.426\fax-0.02\frz-8.9\fry-1.5\blur1.337\c&H342F2F&}Congratulations!\NI don't know your cellphone number either,\Nbut could you give me Takagi's? *lol*
Dialogue: 10,0:08:37.58,0:08:40.16,Default-Italic,,0,0,0,,Why does she want Shuujin's and not mine?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:41.12,0:08:42.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:50.80,0:08:51.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:51.51,0:08:53.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Is Hattori calling again?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:54.05,0:08:55.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The popular ones sure are busy.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:56.44,0:08:58.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? It's a number I don't know.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:58.72,0:08:59.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:59.94,0:09:00.94,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Azuki.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:01.39,0:09:02.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?! Azuki?!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:02.77,0:09:04.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:04.02,0:09:06.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Aren't you calling the wrong person?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:07.31,0:09:08.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Takagi, thank you.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:08.98,0:09:09.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:10.15,0:09:11.86,Default,,0,0,0,,S—Sorry, I'm going out onto the veranda.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:11.86,0:09:13.49,Default,,0,0,0,,What? Why?!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:15.70,0:09:17.32,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you thanking me for?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:17.32,0:09:22.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I've wanted to thank you properly for a while now.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:22.50,0:09:25.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Mashiro and I are always \Nsaying that if it weren't for you,
Dialogue: 10,0:09:25.50,0:09:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,middle school graduation would have been \Nthe end of our feelings for each other.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:30.29,0:09:31.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you really think so?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:31.88,0:09:37.34,Default,,0,0,0,,All I did was ask Saiko to help me out with my \Ndream of wanting to become a manga writer.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:37.34,0:09:38.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It's thanks to that dream.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:38.51,0:09:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Mashiro says that if you \Nhadn't asked him to help you,
Dialogue: 10,0:09:41.76,0:09:45.79,Default,,0,0,0,,he probably would have just been drifting \Nthrough every day without any sort of goal.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:45.79,0:09:48.92,Default,,0,0,0,,He said that you were the \None who gave him his dream.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:48.92,0:09:52.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I told him that he should tell you himself,
Dialogue: 10,0:09:52.15,0:09:54.83,Default,,0,0,0,,but he said it's embarrassing for \Nguys to talk about that kind of stuff.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:55.99,0:09:57.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:58.11,0:10:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,We're still not sure if deciding \Nto become mangakas
Dialogue: 10,0:10:00.44,0:10:03.34,Default,,0,0,0,,will turn out to be a good \Nthing or a bad thing yet, though.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:03.34,0:10:07.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think anything bad can come out of \Nyou doing your best to achieve your dreams.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:10.04,0:10:11.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You're right.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:11.75,0:10:13.55,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing bad about trying your hardest.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:15.05,0:10:17.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess you can talk to boys after all.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:17.77,0:10:21.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I was a bit surprised that \Nyou called me out of the blue.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:21.01,0:10:22.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:25.14,0:10:26.52,Default,,0,0,0,,That's because it's just the phone.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:26.52,0:10:28.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't even see your face.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:28.07,0:10:30.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And I don't like you that way, either.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:30.06,0:10:31.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess that's true.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:32.65,0:10:33.65,Default,,0,0,0,,What the hell?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:33.65,0:10:35.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry, Miyoshi.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:35.11,0:10:36.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Azuki and Shuujin aren't—
Dialogue: 10,0:10:36.61,0:10:39.61,Default,,0,0,0,,What the hell are you two \Ntalking about so cheerfully?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:39.61,0:10:41.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't see something wrong here?!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:41.02,0:10:43.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Miho, Takagi is {\i1}my{\i0} boyfriend!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:43.88,0:10:45.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You should be talking to Mashiro.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:45.70,0:10:46.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:46.53,0:10:47.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:47.33,0:10:48.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes you can.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:48.41,0:10:51.49,Default,,0,0,0,,You should at least tell him \Ncongratulations directly at a time like this.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:51.49,0:10:52.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, Mashiro!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:52.49,0:10:53.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:54.38,0:10:55.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Take it!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:57.84,0:10:59.43,Default-Italic,,0,0,0,,Me, talk to Azuki?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:59.68,0:11:00.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Um—
Dialogue: 10,0:11:02.14,0:11:03.30,Default,,0,0,0,,How long—
Dialogue: 10,0:11:03.30,0:11:05.26,Default,,0,0,0,,How long will you wait for me?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:09.10,0:11:10.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll wait for you.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:14.02,0:11:15.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll wait for you forever.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:20.82,0:11:22.33,Default-Italic,,0,0,0,,We haven't talked since then.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:27.79,0:11:29.16,Default,,0,0,0,,T—This is Mashiro.
